arch:property.oc:show_val: A relatively small unit consisting of mainly sheep/goat long bone fragments. There is also one pig and one dog metapodial. The patina is very even with low/moderate weathering and only a tiny amount of burning. There are no feet and only two cranial fragments. The overall bone density in the unit is fairly low and seems post-consumption. An additional 4mm flotation sample #2, 100% sorted, was completely recorded. This mainly consisted of sheep-sized long bone and unidentifiable fragments, about 20-30% had been burnt at low temperatures and a further c. 5% showed evidence of being burnt at higher temperatures calcining the bone. The few bone fragments that could be identified to the element level showed the presence of of scapula and skull fragments. Last number = 94

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
